##
Write a  program to find the Hailstone Sequence of a given number up to 1.
Example: Input any number (positive) to start for Hailstone Sequence : 13
The hailstone sequence starting at 13 is :                                                               
13  40  20  10  5  16  8  4  2 1 
##
start(){
	piece of num = topiece(bill("Input any positive number to start the Hailstone Sequence : ")+take());
    check(num < 1){ bill("Invalid Input"); serve 1;}
    bill("The hailstone sequence starting from "+tochars(num)+" is :\n"+tochars(num)+" ");
    repeat(num != 1){
    	check(num%2 == 0){
        	num/=2;
            bill(tochars(num)+" ");
        } instead {
        	num = 3 * num + 1;
            bill(tochars(num)+" ");            
        }
    }
}
--end
13
--end
Input any positive number to start the Hailstone Sequence : 13
The hailstone sequence starting from 13 is :
13 40 20 10 5 16 8 4 2 1 